00:00:19.102 --> 00:00:21.646 position:50% align:center
Thank you very much
for your purchase, sir!

00:00:21.730 --> 00:00:22.939 position:50% align:center
And if you have the time,

00:00:23.023 --> 00:00:24.774 position:50% align:center
please come and check out
our afternoon show!

00:00:24.858 --> 00:00:27.944 position:50% align:center
We'll be performing the
B-side track of our CD!

00:00:28.028 --> 00:00:30.363 position:50% align:center
Well now, it's
interesting to find out

00:00:30.447 --> 00:00:32.949 position:50% align:center
which girls the fans
are lining up to see.

00:00:33.033 --> 00:00:34.826 position:50% align:center
Thank you! Take care, now!

00:00:34.909 --> 00:00:36.786 position:50% align:center
[HOHO]
Ino attracts everyone.

00:00:36.870 --> 00:00:38.121 position:50% align:center
[HEMO giggles]

00:00:38.204 --> 00:00:40.457 position:50% align:center
[HOHO] Hemo's popular
among young men and women.

00:00:40.540 --> 00:00:42.792 position:50% align:center
Aw. I'm embarrassed.

00:00:42.876 --> 00:00:44.169 position:50% align:center
[HOHO]
Young girls and middle-aged men

00:00:44.252 --> 00:00:45.670 position:50% align:center
tend to be drawn to Hayu.

00:00:45.754 --> 00:00:47.339 position:50% align:center
Thank you very much!

00:00:47.422 --> 00:00:49.841 position:50% align:center
[HOHO] Nina is popular
among men in general.

00:00:49.924 --> 00:00:51.593 position:50% align:center
[ROKO grumbles]

00:00:51.676 --> 00:00:52.969 position:50% align:center
That leaves Roko.

00:00:53.053 --> 00:00:54.888 position:50% align:center
I'm you're biggest fan, Roko!

00:00:54.971 --> 00:00:57.223 position:50% align:center
[HOHO] Well, she's popular among
women in their 20's and older.

00:00:57.307 --> 00:00:59.309 position:50% align:center
I knew that!

00:00:59.392 --> 00:01:04.397 position:50% align:center line:10%
â™ª

00:02:35.155 --> 00:02:38.033 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:02:40.285 --> 00:02:42.328 position:50% align:center
[NUA]
Dance and Shine!

00:02:54.299 --> 00:02:55.884 position:50% align:center
[INO exhales]

00:02:55.967 --> 00:02:58.178 position:50% align:center
[INO]
I can finally relax for now.

00:02:58.261 --> 00:03:01.973 position:50% align:center
I'm glad Miss Hoho found
a bathroom close to the stage!

00:03:02.057 --> 00:03:03.516 position:50% align:center
The morning show went great!

00:03:03.600 --> 00:03:06.061 position:50% align:center
Just gotta keep it up
for the afternoon, too!

00:03:06.144 --> 00:03:07.687 position:50% align:center
I wonder if I'll
have time go again

00:03:07.771 --> 00:03:09.689 position:50% align:center
right before the next show.

00:03:09.773 --> 00:03:11.149 position:50% align:center
Better make sure to
take care of it now

00:03:11.232 --> 00:03:12.567 position:50% align:center
to avoid any more hiccups.

00:03:12.650 --> 00:03:13.860 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Shoot!

00:03:13.943 --> 00:03:16.446 position:50% align:center
I have to hurry up and
get back to the group!

00:03:16.529 --> 00:03:18.531 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Huh?

00:03:18.615 --> 00:03:20.909 position:50% align:center
[INO]
Huh? You're all here?

00:03:20.992 --> 00:03:22.702 position:50% align:center
Uh?

00:03:22.786 --> 00:03:24.162 position:50% align:center
[gasp]

00:03:24.245 --> 00:03:25.622 position:50% align:center
[INO]
Don't tell me...

00:03:25.705 --> 00:03:28.291 position:50% align:center
I forgot to turn on the privacy
sound machine, didn't I?

00:03:28.375 --> 00:03:31.419 position:50% align:center
Ah! No! Don't worry!
We didn't hear a single thing!

00:03:31.503 --> 00:03:33.880 position:50% align:center
Yeah! We all only
just walked in!

00:03:33.963 --> 00:03:36.257 position:50% align:center
Plus, it's nothing to be
embarrassed about.

00:03:36.341 --> 00:03:38.218 position:50% align:center
It's normal and natural!

00:03:38.301 --> 00:03:39.928 position:50% align:center
You're perfect!

00:03:40.011 --> 00:03:41.721 position:50% align:center
[whimpers]

00:03:44.766 --> 00:03:46.518 position:50% align:center
[INO]
So why are you all here?

00:03:46.601 --> 00:03:48.603 position:50% align:center
Are you nervous
about the show, too?

00:03:48.687 --> 00:03:50.355 position:50% align:center
No, Ino. That's your thing.

00:03:50.438 --> 00:03:53.942 position:50% align:center
We hadn't planned on it,
but Hoho insisted we stop by.

00:03:54.025 --> 00:03:57.070 position:50% align:center
She was talking to somebody
and didn't want us hearing it.

00:03:57.153 --> 00:03:58.405 position:50% align:center
--[door opens]
--[INO grunts]

00:03:58.488 --> 00:04:01.991 position:50% align:center
The debt... I can't.
It's impossible to repay it.

00:04:02.075 --> 00:04:04.786 position:50% align:center
There's no coming back.
It's game over.

00:04:04.869 --> 00:04:07.080 position:50% align:center
That's it. It's been great.

00:04:07.163 --> 00:04:08.665 position:50% align:center
Thanks for everything.

00:04:08.748 --> 00:04:11.084 position:50% align:center
Maybe we'll meet again one day
at the hot springs in the sky.

00:04:11.167 --> 00:04:13.795 position:50% align:center
W-W-W-Wait!
Are you okay, Miss Hoho?

00:04:13.878 --> 00:04:14.963 position:50% align:center
[HOHO]
Play the game.

00:04:15.046 --> 00:04:16.381 position:50% align:center
Hope.

00:04:16.464 --> 00:04:19.134 position:50% align:center
Starting tomorrow,

00:04:19.217 --> 00:04:22.721 position:50% align:center
we may never be able
to eat meat again!

00:04:22.804 --> 00:04:24.389 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Huh? What do you mean?

00:04:24.472 --> 00:04:27.058 position:50% align:center
Why are we talking
about this in here?

00:04:27.142 --> 00:04:28.977 position:50% align:center
Hey, everyone! Uh.

00:04:29.060 --> 00:04:30.645 position:50% align:center
What did I walk in on?

00:04:32.355 --> 00:04:33.690 position:50% align:center
[HOHO]
Here's what's up.

00:04:33.773 --> 00:04:36.192 position:50% align:center
That call I received was
from one of the higher-ups.

00:04:36.276 --> 00:04:37.527 position:50% align:center
[GROUP gasps]

00:04:37.610 --> 00:04:40.113 position:50% align:center
[HOHO] We sell 1,000
copies of the CD today,

00:04:40.196 --> 00:04:41.573 position:50% align:center
or there will be consequences.

00:04:41.656 --> 00:04:44.993 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
What? One thousand copies?!

00:04:45.076 --> 00:04:48.496 position:50% align:center
See? This is why you don't print
3,000 copies on your first run!

00:04:48.580 --> 00:04:50.498 position:50% align:center
That's <i>sanzen</i> in Japanese!

00:04:50.582 --> 00:04:52.375 position:50% align:center
Wait! Why are you
speaking Japanese?

00:04:52.459 --> 00:04:53.877 position:50% align:center
--[HAYU] It's cool!
--[NINA] What?

00:04:53.960 --> 00:04:56.254 position:50% align:center
How many copies did
we end up selling anyway?

00:04:56.338 --> 00:04:59.883 position:50% align:center
Well, we sold 500 copies
before the morning show.

00:04:59.966 --> 00:05:01.634 position:50% align:center
So that means
we're halfway there!

00:05:01.718 --> 00:05:02.510 position:50% align:center
That's right!

00:05:02.594 --> 00:05:04.929 position:50% align:center
Yeah, but...

00:05:05.013 --> 00:05:06.556 position:50% align:center
Typically, at these events

00:05:06.639 --> 00:05:08.808 position:50% align:center
most of your sales
are earlier in the day.

00:05:08.892 --> 00:05:09.893 position:50% align:center
[GROUP gasps]

00:05:09.976 --> 00:05:11.227 position:50% align:center
[TONE]
The hardcore fans have been here

00:05:11.311 --> 00:05:13.104 position:50% align:center
since before the first show,

00:05:13.188 --> 00:05:15.190 position:50% align:center
and they already bought
a bunch of merchandise.

00:05:15.273 --> 00:05:16.191 position:50% align:center
[GROUP sighs]

00:05:16.274 --> 00:05:17.817 position:50% align:center
That's true, I guess.

00:05:17.901 --> 00:05:19.402 position:50% align:center
Well,

00:05:19.486 --> 00:05:24.949 position:50% align:center
maybe sales will go up if you
added a new perk or something?

00:05:25.033 --> 00:05:28.620 position:50% align:center
What do you think it should be?

00:05:28.703 --> 00:05:30.246 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Stare...

00:05:30.330 --> 00:05:32.749 position:50% align:center
[NINA] Wait! Why is
everyone staring at me?

00:05:32.832 --> 00:05:34.000 position:50% align:center
--[ROKO] Yes, I see.
--[INO] Yup!

00:05:34.084 --> 00:05:35.418 position:50% align:center
It's an option.

00:05:35.502 --> 00:05:38.421 position:50% align:center
No! We can't add a perk
to only the afternoon half!

00:05:38.505 --> 00:05:40.840 position:50% align:center
That would be unfair
to the morning fans!

00:05:40.924 --> 00:05:41.966 position:50% align:center
[GROUP gasps]

00:05:42.050 --> 00:05:43.510 position:50% align:center
Good point!
And completely unexpected.

00:05:43.593 --> 00:05:45.470 position:50% align:center
[NINA] The hardcore fans bought
their stuff in the morning,

00:05:45.553 --> 00:05:46.971 position:50% align:center
so they would miss out
on the extra perk!

00:05:47.055 --> 00:05:48.890 position:50% align:center
Oh! That would be really unfair!

00:05:48.973 --> 00:05:50.100 position:50% align:center
Yeah! That's right!

00:05:50.183 --> 00:05:53.144 position:50% align:center
What we need here is
a full frontal attack!

00:05:53.228 --> 00:05:54.479 position:50% align:center
We just gotta
kick it up a notch,

00:05:54.562 --> 00:05:56.356 position:50% align:center
so they'll wanna
buy even more stuff!

00:05:56.439 --> 00:05:57.857 position:50% align:center
Great idea!

00:05:57.941 --> 00:05:59.359 position:50% align:center
But what does that mean?

00:05:59.442 --> 00:06:01.653 position:50% align:center
How exactly do we
kick it up a notch?

00:06:01.736 --> 00:06:04.572 position:50% align:center
[TONE] Hmmm. That's
a very good question.

00:06:04.656 --> 00:06:08.451 position:50% align:center
[ROKO] Nina! Tone! Let's execute
the full frontal attack!

00:06:08.535 --> 00:06:10.161 position:50% align:center
You will have to be resourceful!

00:06:10.245 --> 00:06:12.163 position:50% align:center
Why do you have to
single me out again?!

00:06:12.247 --> 00:06:14.374 position:50% align:center
Yeah, and what'd I do?

00:06:14.457 --> 00:06:16.042 position:50% align:center
[ROKO]
You know, come to think of it,

00:06:16.126 --> 00:06:18.545 position:50% align:center
we've never even had a
discussion about this before.

00:06:18.628 --> 00:06:21.131 position:50% align:center
We've been more focused on
ourselves than our fans.

00:06:21.214 --> 00:06:24.259 position:50% align:center
We were too concerned about
our performances to consider it.

00:06:24.342 --> 00:06:25.552 position:50% align:center
It's a clear reminder that

00:06:25.635 --> 00:06:27.637 position:50% align:center
we still have a
long way to go as idols.

00:06:27.721 --> 00:06:29.389 position:50% align:center
You may be right, Ino.

00:06:29.472 --> 00:06:32.225 position:50% align:center
All we've done to train
is watch Cream Anmitsu.

00:06:32.308 --> 00:06:35.020 position:50% align:center
Hey, you guys! I think
I know what'll help!

00:06:35.103 --> 00:06:37.022 position:50% align:center
We should use more
"call and response"

00:06:37.105 --> 00:06:38.398 position:50% align:center
in the afternoon show.

00:06:38.481 --> 00:06:39.149 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:06:39.232 --> 00:06:40.483 position:50% align:center
Cream Anmitsu does.

00:06:40.567 --> 00:06:42.694 position:50% align:center
And it always gets their
audiences really fired up!

00:06:42.777 --> 00:06:43.570 position:50% align:center
[GROUP gasps]

00:06:43.653 --> 00:06:45.071 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah!

00:06:45.155 --> 00:06:47.657 position:50% align:center
Okay, but what do you mean by
"call and response" Hemo?

00:06:47.741 --> 00:06:50.326 position:50% align:center
--[GROUP] Huh?
--[INO stammers]

00:06:50.410 --> 00:06:53.580 position:50% align:center
I mean how would you do it?

00:06:53.663 --> 00:06:55.206 position:50% align:center
I can show you.

00:06:55.290 --> 00:06:57.125 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:06:57.208 --> 00:06:58.918 position:50% align:center
[HEMO]
Let's put it this way.

00:06:59.002 --> 00:07:01.338 position:50% align:center
It's like merging
our voices into one.

00:07:01.421 --> 00:07:05.300 position:50% align:center
And it's really
quite enjoyable Ino.

00:07:05.383 --> 00:07:08.345 position:50% align:center
So, what do you say,
huh? Wanna try?

00:07:08.428 --> 00:07:10.221 position:50% align:center
I think you're
really going to like it.

00:07:10.305 --> 00:07:11.348 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:07:11.431 --> 00:07:13.391 position:50% align:center
Stop! The mood is wrong!

00:07:13.475 --> 00:07:15.769 position:50% align:center
It's more energetic,
not romantic, okay?

00:07:15.852 --> 00:07:16.936 position:50% align:center
The mood?

00:07:17.020 --> 00:07:18.897 position:50% align:center
Yeah! It's, like,
loud and you yell stuff,

00:07:18.980 --> 00:07:21.107 position:50% align:center
like, "are you all ready?"
and, "let's go!"

00:07:21.191 --> 00:07:23.651 position:50% align:center
Oh! Right, I've
seen that before!

00:07:23.735 --> 00:07:25.236 position:50% align:center
[HAYU]
Uh, okay then.

00:07:25.320 --> 00:07:27.655 position:50% align:center
It was short and sweet at the
Cream Anmitsu concert, right?

00:07:27.739 --> 00:07:29.866 position:50% align:center
Yeah, it was!
Their fans loved it;

00:07:29.949 --> 00:07:31.910 position:50% align:center
they had this great back
and forth with them!

00:07:31.993 --> 00:07:34.079 position:50% align:center
Thanks for coming
out today, everybody!

00:07:34.162 --> 00:07:37.040 position:50% align:center
Hey, guys! It's time to get
this show on the road!

00:07:37.123 --> 00:07:40.043 position:50% align:center
I hope all of you are ready
to jump around and get crazy!

00:07:40.126 --> 00:07:42.420 position:50% align:center
[CROWD]
Yeah!

00:07:44.089 --> 00:07:45.548 position:50% align:center
Short and sweet?

00:07:45.632 --> 00:07:48.718 position:50% align:center
I guess in retrospect, we
probably should've asked Chiko

00:07:48.802 --> 00:07:50.303 position:50% align:center
for more advice than we did.

00:07:50.387 --> 00:07:51.763 position:50% align:center
[ROKO]
Why don't we ask her now?

00:07:51.846 --> 00:07:52.806 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Huh?

00:07:52.889 --> 00:07:54.057 position:50% align:center
[INO]
Are you sure?

00:07:54.140 --> 00:07:57.227 position:50% align:center
Chiko's a popular idol.
She's probably too busy.

00:07:57.310 --> 00:08:00.355 position:50% align:center
[phone rings]

00:08:00.438 --> 00:08:07.028 position:50% align:center
--[CHIKO'S phone rings]
--[GROUP] Huh?

00:08:07.112 --> 00:08:08.613 position:50% align:center
Chiko... Seriously?

00:08:08.697 --> 00:08:11.741 position:50% align:center
[CHIKO] It's not what you think!
No need to be creeped out.

00:08:11.825 --> 00:08:14.661 position:50% align:center
All I wanted was to come
here to privately support you.

00:08:14.744 --> 00:08:15.870 position:50% align:center
And then you were there

00:08:15.954 --> 00:08:17.622 position:50% align:center
and I couldn't just
walk out of the stall.

00:08:17.706 --> 00:08:20.125 position:50% align:center
[INO gasps] Does that mean
you heard everything we said?

00:08:20.208 --> 00:08:21.543 position:50% align:center
Oh, what a mess.

00:08:21.626 --> 00:08:22.669 position:50% align:center
You okay?

00:08:22.752 --> 00:08:24.212 position:50% align:center
I was trying to find
a place to change.

00:08:24.295 --> 00:08:25.505 position:50% align:center
Riri suggested here.

00:08:25.588 --> 00:08:26.840 position:50% align:center
[HAYU gasps]

00:08:27.924 --> 00:08:29.968 position:50% align:center
[CHIKO] I can only buy ten
copies at a time, right?

00:08:30.051 --> 00:08:31.761 position:50% align:center
Yes. That is correct.

00:08:31.845 --> 00:08:33.096 position:50% align:center
[HAYU]
That hat of yours!

00:08:33.179 --> 00:08:34.806 position:50% align:center
I've seen it at every
single one of our events!

00:08:34.889 --> 00:08:36.141 position:50% align:center
[CHIKO gasps]

00:08:36.224 --> 00:08:39.144 position:50% align:center
Yeah. I remember seeing
that hat a bunch, too.

00:08:39.227 --> 00:08:42.272 position:50% align:center
I don't have as many female
fans, so it stood out to me.

00:08:42.355 --> 00:08:45.692 position:50% align:center
So, were you here since
before the morning concert?

00:08:45.775 --> 00:08:47.777 position:50% align:center
[CHIKO]
Y-You're all over-reacting.

00:08:47.861 --> 00:08:50.530 position:50% align:center
I wouldn't even be here
if my big sister wasn't!

00:08:50.613 --> 00:08:52.949 position:50% align:center
Ooh! Chiko really is a <i>tsundere</i> !

00:08:53.033 --> 00:08:55.326 position:50% align:center
Don't feel like you have
to pretend in front of us.

00:08:55.410 --> 00:09:00.040 position:50% align:center
[INO gasps] Oh, my! How many
CDs did you buy, anyway?

00:09:01.166 --> 00:09:02.375 position:50% align:center
[GROUP sighs]

00:09:02.459 --> 00:09:03.918 position:50% align:center
Chiko.

00:09:04.002 --> 00:09:06.504 position:50% align:center
[CHIKO] What?! No! I bought
these for my big sister--not me!

00:09:08.548 --> 00:09:09.632 position:50% align:center
[yelps]

00:09:09.716 --> 00:09:11.301 position:50% align:center
[INO] If you could
shake hands with Roko

00:09:11.384 --> 00:09:14.888 position:50% align:center
all day would you
consider buying 500 more?

00:09:14.971 --> 00:09:17.724 position:50% align:center
500 copies? For the whole day?

00:09:17.807 --> 00:09:20.185 position:50% align:center
Enough! Cut it out, you two!

00:09:20.268 --> 00:09:22.062 position:50% align:center
[HOHO]
Meat. I love meat.

00:09:22.145 --> 00:09:22.896 position:50% align:center
Meat...

00:09:22.979 --> 00:09:25.273 position:50% align:center
You okay?

00:09:25.357 --> 00:09:28.068 position:50% align:center
[CHIKO]
What? How to fire up your crowd?

00:09:28.151 --> 00:09:30.320 position:50% align:center
I know you're desperate, but
it's not like I can give you

00:09:30.403 --> 00:09:32.989 position:50% align:center
an entire routine
this last minute.

00:09:33.073 --> 00:09:35.575 position:50% align:center
We started out performing
in public parks, too.

00:09:35.658 --> 00:09:37.327 position:50% align:center
We suffered through
the tiny crowds

00:09:37.410 --> 00:09:39.329 position:50% align:center
and worked hard to
eventually get where we are.

00:09:39.412 --> 00:09:40.747 position:50% align:center
[ROKO sighs]

00:09:40.830 --> 00:09:41.748 position:50% align:center
That makes sense.

00:09:41.831 --> 00:09:43.458 position:50% align:center
[CHIKO]
Oh.

00:09:43.541 --> 00:09:45.669 position:50% align:center
[ROKO]
Hmm.

00:09:45.752 --> 00:09:47.712 position:50% align:center
[CHIKO]
Mmm...

00:09:47.796 --> 00:09:48.922 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:09:49.005 --> 00:09:50.131 position:50% align:center
[ROKO grunts]

00:09:50.215 --> 00:09:51.466 position:50% align:center
[CHIKO]
But...

00:09:51.549 --> 00:09:53.093 position:50% align:center
But what? [gasps]

00:09:53.176 --> 00:09:54.719 position:50% align:center
If you had asked me like this,

00:09:54.803 --> 00:09:58.056 position:50% align:center
"I love you, Big Sis Chiko.
Won't you help me please?"

00:09:58.139 --> 00:10:00.058 position:50% align:center
Then I think I might have
some more advice to give you.

00:10:00.141 --> 00:10:02.352 position:50% align:center
[ROKO] But I am the
big sister, you creep!

00:10:02.435 --> 00:10:05.021 position:50% align:center
[CROWD chatters]

00:10:05.105 --> 00:10:07.023 position:50% align:center
Nice! I see new customers

00:10:07.107 --> 00:10:09.109 position:50% align:center
