00:19:53.401 --> 00:19:56.071 position:50% align:center
[ROKO]
Oh, gee, how considerate of you.

00:19:56.154 --> 00:19:58.239 position:50% align:center
All right! The ones
in charge of cooking

00:19:58.323 --> 00:19:59.824 position:50% align:center
are these two!

00:19:59.908 --> 00:20:02.410 position:50% align:center
Miss Sakura and Hemo!

00:20:02.494 --> 00:20:03.912 position:50% align:center
[GROUP giggles]

00:20:03.995 --> 00:20:06.373 position:50% align:center
[TONE] And I've got these for
the the foodies out there:

00:20:06.456 --> 00:20:08.792 position:50% align:center
Tone's special
food deflection aprons!

00:20:08.875 --> 00:20:10.168 position:50% align:center
[GROUP giggles]

00:20:10.251 --> 00:20:12.712 position:50% align:center
I see why you're
the <i>okonomiyaki</i> girl!

00:20:12.796 --> 00:20:15.715 position:50% align:center
Now we don't need to worry
about ruining our costumes.

00:20:15.799 --> 00:20:16.841 position:50% align:center
[ROKO grunts]

00:20:16.925 --> 00:20:19.803 position:50% align:center
[TONE]
We don't have any smalls.

00:20:19.886 --> 00:20:21.388 position:50% align:center
[ROKO]
You liar.

00:20:21.471 --> 00:20:24.474 position:50% align:center
All right!
Hemo, let's get started!

00:20:24.557 --> 00:20:26.559 position:50% align:center
Okay! I'm ready to go!

00:20:26.643 --> 00:20:29.562 position:50% align:center
Thanks for helping me!
This is going to be so fun.

00:20:29.646 --> 00:20:31.523 position:50% align:center
Yeah! This is
a great opportunity

00:20:31.606 --> 00:20:33.441 position:50% align:center
for me to practice my cooking!

00:20:33.525 --> 00:20:34.734 position:50% align:center
'Cause if you haven't noticed,

00:20:34.818 --> 00:20:36.403 position:50% align:center
I've been doing
more of it lately.

00:20:36.486 --> 00:20:38.071 position:50% align:center
[HAYU growls]

00:20:38.154 --> 00:20:41.449 position:50% align:center
Ready? Let's start making
<i>okonomiyaki</i> together, okay?

00:20:41.533 --> 00:20:42.826 position:50% align:center
Yup!

00:20:42.909 --> 00:20:45.245 position:50% align:center
[INO] Pour a thin layer
of the batter on the grill.

00:20:45.328 --> 00:20:47.455 position:50% align:center
[HEMO] Mix all the
ingredients in the bowl.

00:20:47.539 --> 00:20:49.124 position:50% align:center
[INO] Layer the cabbage
and ingredients

00:20:49.207 --> 00:20:50.792 position:50% align:center
and top it off with an egg!

00:20:50.875 --> 00:20:52.794 position:50% align:center
[HEMO] Incorporate
as much air as you can

00:20:52.877 --> 00:20:54.379 position:50% align:center
and gently mold it to shape!

00:20:54.462 --> 00:20:56.006 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
What?!

00:20:56.089 --> 00:20:57.382 position:50% align:center
Hemo.

00:20:57.465 --> 00:20:58.758 position:50% align:center
Miss Ino.

00:20:58.842 --> 00:20:59.759 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Don't tell me...

00:20:59.843 --> 00:21:01.803 position:50% align:center
Not good! No!

00:21:01.886 --> 00:21:04.848 position:50% align:center
The classic Osaka vs
Hiroshima-style <i>okonomiyaki</i>

00:21:04.931 --> 00:21:06.850 position:50% align:center
debate has broken out!

00:21:10.103 --> 00:21:14.024 position:50% align:center
My dad is from Osaka originally,
and my mom is from Hiroshima,

00:21:14.107 --> 00:21:15.692 position:50% align:center
so this dispute caused
a tremendous rift

00:21:15.775 --> 00:21:18.528 position:50% align:center
between their families right at
the beginning of their marriage!

00:21:18.611 --> 00:21:21.406 position:50% align:center
It did? So then how did it end?

00:21:21.489 --> 00:21:23.783 position:50% align:center
It looks like the battle
lines have been drawn.

00:21:23.867 --> 00:21:26.578 position:50% align:center
I can't believe you're
taking their side, too, Nina.

00:21:26.661 --> 00:21:30.373 position:50% align:center
How could you when you both
have great Osaka-style figures!

00:21:30.457 --> 00:21:32.083 position:50% align:center
Stop talking about my body!

00:21:32.167 --> 00:21:33.626 position:50% align:center
Look!

00:21:33.710 --> 00:21:36.087 position:50% align:center
Osaka-style is fluffier and
the batter is really delicious!

00:21:36.171 --> 00:21:38.673 position:50% align:center
Hiroshima-style brings out
the flavor of each ingredient--

00:21:38.757 --> 00:21:39.758 position:50% align:center
there's no contest!

00:21:39.841 --> 00:21:41.843 position:50% align:center
All right!
It's time to settle this!

00:21:41.926 --> 00:21:44.471 position:50% align:center
Fine, let's just ask the
<i>okonomiyaki</i> specialist!

00:21:44.554 --> 00:21:45.597 position:50% align:center
Wait! Not me!

00:21:45.680 --> 00:21:46.681 position:50% align:center
[ROKO]
We wanna know what you think

00:21:46.765 --> 00:21:48.725 position:50% align:center
as a person with
ties to both styles!

00:21:48.808 --> 00:21:50.101 position:50% align:center
Leave me out of it!

00:21:50.185 --> 00:21:53.355 position:50% align:center
Fine, well, I think...

00:21:53.438 --> 00:21:54.606 position:50% align:center
You think...?

00:21:54.689 --> 00:21:56.107 position:50% align:center
[TONE]
I think <i>mojayaki's</i> the best!

00:21:56.191 --> 00:21:57.359 position:50% align:center
--[GROUP gasps]
--[ROKO] Tokyo-style?

00:21:57.442 --> 00:21:58.610 position:50% align:center
Well, yeah, I mean...

00:21:58.693 --> 00:22:00.236 position:50% align:center
I got hooked on it
since the first time

00:22:00.320 --> 00:22:02.197 position:50% align:center
I tried it when I moved here.

00:22:02.280 --> 00:22:05.492 position:50% align:center
Truth is I love both
Osaka and Hiroshima-styles!

00:22:05.575 --> 00:22:07.869 position:50% align:center
Either way, it's still
the most cost-effective dish

00:22:07.952 --> 00:22:10.830 position:50% align:center
that basically just uses flour
and cabbage as ingredients!

00:22:10.914 --> 00:22:13.667 position:50% align:center
[ROKO] That's not exactly
a ringing endorsement.

00:22:13.750 --> 00:22:16.044 position:50% align:center
[TONE] So, lets agree that
they're both awesome!

00:22:16.127 --> 00:22:18.672 position:50% align:center
This is supposed to be
a celebration after all.

00:22:18.755 --> 00:22:19.923 position:50% align:center
Let's eat and make up.

00:22:20.006 --> 00:22:21.549 position:50% align:center
That sounds good to me.

00:22:21.633 --> 00:22:22.634 position:50% align:center
Shall we finish it off?

00:22:22.717 --> 00:22:24.427 position:50% align:center
[INO giggles]
Yeah!

00:22:24.511 --> 00:22:25.887 position:50% align:center
--[INO] With mustard-mayo!
--[ROKO] With only mayo!

00:22:25.970 --> 00:22:26.971 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
What?!

00:22:27.055 --> 00:22:28.848 position:50% align:center
Are you kidding?!

00:22:31.017 --> 00:22:32.060 position:50% align:center
[INO]
Tone!

00:22:32.143 --> 00:22:34.396 position:50% align:center
We'd all like you to have this.

00:22:34.479 --> 00:22:38.233 position:50% align:center
W-Wait a minute! An autographed
copy of your debut CD?

00:22:38.316 --> 00:22:42.946 position:50% align:center
Listen, this is to thank you
for everything you've done.

00:22:43.029 --> 00:22:44.322 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:22:44.406 --> 00:22:46.533 position:50% align:center
[INO] I'm sorry, but I'm afraid
we don't have money,

00:22:46.616 --> 00:22:48.368 position:50% align:center
so this is all we can do.

00:22:48.451 --> 00:22:49.744 position:50% align:center
We appreciate you.

00:22:49.828 --> 00:22:51.454 position:50% align:center
Thank you, Tonecchi!

00:22:51.538 --> 00:22:52.706 position:50% align:center
You take care of us!

00:22:52.789 --> 00:22:54.207 position:50% align:center
You've helped us all so much.

00:22:54.290 --> 00:22:56.126 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:22:58.920 --> 00:23:00.422 position:50% align:center
[TONE]
No, this is great.

00:23:00.505 --> 00:23:03.049 position:50% align:center
It's the best gift you
could ever give me!

00:23:03.133 --> 00:23:05.260 position:50% align:center
Thanks, everyone.
I'll cherish it,

00:23:05.343 --> 00:23:08.054 position:50% align:center
especially since your show
probably won't get renewed.

00:23:08.138 --> 00:23:08.930 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Huh?

00:23:09.014 --> 00:23:10.181 position:50% align:center
What do you mean?

00:23:10.265 --> 00:23:11.850 position:50% align:center
Not get renewed?

00:23:11.933 --> 00:23:17.856 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
What?!

00:23:20.483 --> 00:23:21.818 position:50% align:center
[HOHO]
Hmph!

00:23:24.654 --> 00:23:28.700 position:50% align:center
[HOHO] Coming at you next time
on <i>Dropout Idol Fruit Tart</i> !

00:23:30.285 --> 00:23:31.411 position:50% align:center
Nua here!

00:23:31.494 --> 00:23:32.871 position:50% align:center
Hey, I only appeared announcing

00:23:32.954 --> 00:23:35.623 position:50% align:center
the episode title and in the
midpoint break this time!

00:23:35.707 --> 00:23:38.835 position:50% align:center
In fact, I barely have
any scenes next time, too!

00:23:38.918 --> 00:23:40.545 position:50% align:center
I'll just have to show
Fruit Tart a thing or two

00:23:40.628 --> 00:23:42.839 position:50% align:center
in the National Idol
